{
  "title": "Global and Local Scope",
  "cells": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<div><div class=\"article__inner\" style=\"margin: 0px auto; box-sizing: border-box; max-width: none; width: 272px; font-family: 'Open Sans', 'Hevetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><div class=\"article__header\" style=\"margin-top: 35px; box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\"><div class=\"lesson-checkpoint__name\" style=\"font-size: 25px; line-height: 1.15; color: rgb(66, 66, 66); font-weight: bold; box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">Global vs Local Variables</div></div><div class=\"article__content\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\"><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">Let's talk about an important concept:<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">scope</strong>. Scope can be global or local.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">Variables defined&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">outside</strong>&nbsp;a function are accessible anywhere once they have been declared. They are called<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">global variables</strong>&nbsp;and their scope is<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">global</strong>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">For example:</p><pre style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(197, 200, 198); border-radius: 2px; overflow: auto; padding: 7px 10px; background-color: rgb(35, 44, 49);\"><code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: 1.5; border-top-left-radius: 2px; border-top-right-radius: 2px; border-bottom-right-radius: 2px; border-bottom-left-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(178, 148, 187);\">var</span> globalVar = <span class=\"string\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(181, 189, 104);\">\"hello\"</span>;\n\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(178, 148, 187);\">var</span> foo = <span class=\"function\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(178, 148, 187);\">function</span><span class=\"params\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">()</span> {</span>\n    console.log(globalVar);  <span class=\"comment\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(150, 152, 150); font-style: italic;\">// prints \"hello\"</span>\n}\n</code></pre><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">The variable&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">globalVar</code>&nbsp;can be accessed anywhere, even inside the function&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">foo</code>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">Variables defined&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">inside</strong>&nbsp;a function are<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">local variables</strong>. They cannot be accessed outside of that function.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">For example:</p><pre style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(197, 200, 198); border-radius: 2px; overflow: auto; padding: 7px 10px; background-color: rgb(35, 44, 49);\"><code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: 1.5; border-top-left-radius: 2px; border-top-right-radius: 2px; border-bottom-right-radius: 2px; border-bottom-left-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(178, 148, 187);\">var</span> bar = <span class=\"function\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(178, 148, 187);\">function</span><span class=\"params\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">()</span> {</span>\n    <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(178, 148, 187);\">var</span> localVar = <span class=\"string\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(181, 189, 104);\">\"howdy\"</span>;\n}\n\nconsole.log(localVar);  <span class=\"comment\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); color: rgb(150, 152, 150); font-style: italic;\">// error</span>\n</code></pre><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">The variable&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">localVar</code>&nbsp;only exists inside the function&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">bar</code>. Trying to print&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">localVar</code>&nbsp;outside the function gives a error.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">Check out the code in the editor. Until now you've been using the&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>keyword without really understanding why. The&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>&nbsp;keyword creates a new variable&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">in the current scope</strong>. That means if&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>&nbsp;is used outside a function, that variable has a global scope. If&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>&nbsp;is used inside a function, that variable has a local scope.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">On&nbsp;<a class=\"line-no\" data-from=\"4\" data-to=\"\" style=\"color: inherit; box-sizing: border-box; cursor: text; transition: color 0.1s linear, background-color 0.2s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.1s linear, border-radius 0.2s ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: color 0.1s linear, background-color 0.2s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.1s linear, border-radius 0.2s ease-in-out; outline: 0px;\">line 4</a>&nbsp;we have not used the&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>keyword, so when we log&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">my_number</code>to the console outside of the function, it will be 14.</p></div></div><div class=\"lesson-checkpoint__instructions\" style=\"position: relative; padding: 0px 0px 25px; margin-top: 55px; border-top-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(197, 223, 234); border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(197, 223, 234); box-sizing: border-box; font-family: 'Open Sans', 'Hevetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; widows: 1; background-color: rgb(240, 250, 255);\"><div class=\"article__inner lesson-checkpoint__instructions__header\" style=\"position: relative; top: -1.25em; left: -0.65em; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(66, 66, 66); text-align: center; margin: 0px auto; box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); max-width: none; width: 272px;\"><div class=\"block-label--light-blue\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 0px 0.65em; height: 2.5em; line-height: 2.4em; font-weight: bold; white-space: nowrap; border: 1px solid rgb(197, 223, 234); box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Instructions</div></div><div class=\"article__inner\" style=\"margin: 0px auto; box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); max-width: none; width: 272px;\"><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">Change&nbsp;<a class=\"line-no\" data-from=\"4\" data-to=\"\" style=\"color: inherit; box-sizing: border-box; cursor: text; transition: color 0.1s linear, background-color 0.2s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.1s linear, border-radius 0.2s ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: color 0.1s linear, background-color 0.2s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.1s linear, border-radius 0.2s ease-in-out; outline: 0px;\">line 4</a>&nbsp;to use the&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>&nbsp;keyword. Notice that the value of&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">my_number</code>&nbsp;in the function is now 14 and outside the function is 7.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 18px; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; box-sizing: border-box;\">Using&nbsp;<code class=\"undefined\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\">my_number</code>&nbsp;without the&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>keyword refers to the&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">global</strong>&nbsp;variable that has already been declared outside the function in&nbsp;<a class=\"line-no\" data-from=\"1\" data-to=\"\" style=\"color: inherit; box-sizing: border-box; cursor: text; transition: color 0.1s linear, background-color 0.2s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.1s linear, border-radius 0.2s ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: color 0.1s linear, background-color 0.2s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.1s linear, border-radius 0.2s ease-in-out; outline: 0px;\">line 1</a>. However, if you use the&nbsp;<code class=\"javascript\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); padding: 0.15em 0.25em; font-size: 0.85em; line-height: inherit; border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0666667); font-family: Monaco, Menlo, 'Ubuntu Mono', Consolas, source-code-pro, monospace; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);\">var</span></code>&nbsp;keyword inside a function, it declares a new<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">local</strong>&nbsp;variable that only exists within that function.</p></div></div></div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "data": "var my_number = 7; //this has global scope\n\nvar timesTwo = function(number) {\n    var my_number = number * 2;\n    console.log(\"Inside the function my_number is: \");\n    console.log(my_number);\n}; \n\ntimesTwo(7);\n\nconsole.log(\"Outside the function my_number is: \")\nconsole.log(my_number);"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<div>Result:</div><div><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Inside the function my_number is:&nbsp;</span></div><div>14</div><div>Outside the function my_number is:&nbsp;</div><div>7</div>"
    }
  ]
}